snippet.textDisplay:
Ghost of Yotei should not be on the list. Just like the first game, the sequel is full of ill fitting anachronisms and American colloquialisms that take the player completely out of the setting and history.

Also the Japanese track is pretty spot on and well spoken (except for a few modernized kanji here and there). But the English dub sounds like Americans putting on contrived vaguely offensive stereotype Japanese accented English. Just like the first game, Sucker Punch and SCE should have made the second game Japanese only with subtitles but the game would have sold a lot less units because Americans don't like to read.

snippet.textDisplay: Not gonna lie, the Kingdom Come boys got done dirty. Both of these clips are from the intro of the game, _before_ even the combat tutorial, while most of the other clips are from actually emotional scenes. Just 10-15 minutes later things go horribly wrong, that part already has more interesting performances to pick from. From that it's not much longer until the part where they bicker in the stocks, also a more emotionally charged scene. Several hours (usually at least 25, and that's me lowballing it) later, you get For Whom The Bell Tolls, which is followed by some of the biggest emotional highs and lows of the first region, and that's only the first half of the game! I mean, come on!
